Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone.  After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand for a while, and he could only type 6 words per minute. What is the difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm
Before he broke his arm, Cam could type 9 words per minute, so in 5 minutes he would have typed 45 words (9 x 5). After he broke his arm and was only able to type with one hand at a slower rate of 6 words per minute, he would have typed 30 words in 5 minutes (6 x 5). Therefore, the difference between the number of words he could type before and after he broke his arm is 45 - 30 = 15 words.
